The paper deals with the problem of image cropping using deep learning methods, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model aims to unveil the intrinsic mechanism of aesthetic evaluation, which involves understanding the composition and saliency of an image, and requires the network to be both composition-aware and saliency-aware. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves localizing aesthetically important regions in an image.
